OL,5,Cfindings
OL,7,F"So to us that was the fault. But the
OL,8,FPost Office didn't accept that as
OL,9,Fbeing the fault.
OL,11,F"They said, 'No, you've stolen the
OL,12,Fmoney'."
OL,14,FTo cover the continuous losses, Shane
OL,15,Fran up a huge overdraft and had to
OL,16,Fplunder his savings.
OL,18,FAt the time he was a single father-of-
OL,19,Ftwo and the strain soon took its toll
OL,20,Fon family life.
