OL,3,C'Will it ever be put right?': Ex-
OL,4,Csubpostmasters on Post Office inquiry
OL,5,Cfindings
OL,7,FA statement from the Post Office said:
OL,8,F"The Inquiry has brought to life the
OL,9,Fdevastating stories of those impacted
OL,10,Fby the Horizon Scandal. Their
OL,11,Fexperiences represent a shameful
OL,12,Fperiod in our history.
OL,14,F"Today, we apologise unreservedly for
OL,15,Fthe suffering which Post Office caused
OL,16,Fto postmasters and their loved ones.
OL,17,FWe will carefully consider the report
OL,18,Fand its recommendations."
OL,20,FWhat does the government say?
